ğŸŒ What is HTML?

**HTML (HyperText Markup Language)** is the **standard language used to create web pages**.

* Defines the **structure** of a webpage
* Tells the browser **what content to show**
* Used to create headings, paragraphs, images, links, forms, etc.

ğŸ“Œ HTML is the **foundation of web development**

---

ğŸ†• What is HTML5?

**HTML5** is the **latest and modern version of HTML** designed to support:

* Modern web applications
* Multimedia content
* Mobile-friendly websites
* Better performance and accessibility

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸš€ Why HTML5 is Important

* Supported by all modern browsers
* No need for external plugins (Flash, etc.)
* Built-in audio and video support
* Better SEO and accessibility
* Works well with CSS3 and JavaScript

---

ğŸ†š HTML vs HTML5

| HTML                 | HTML5                  |
| -------------------- | ---------------------- |
| Older version        | Latest version         |
| Limited multimedia   | Built-in audio & video |
| Heavy use of `<div>` | Semantic tags          |
| Less mobile support  | Mobile-friendly        |

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§± Basic Structure of an HTML5 Document

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>HTML5 Introduction</title>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>Welcome to HTML5</h1>
  <p>This is my first HTML5 page.</p>
</body>
</html>
```

ğŸ” Explanation

* `<!DOCTYPE html>` â†’ Declares HTML5
* `<html>` â†’ Root element
* `<head>` â†’ Metadata (title, charset)
* `<body>` â†’ Visible webpage content

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ·ï¸ Semantic Elements in HTML5

Semantic tags clearly describe **their meaning**.

| Tag         | Purpose             |
| ----------- | ------------------- |
| `<header>`  | Page header         |
| `<nav>`     | Navigation links    |
| `<section>` | Section of content  |
| `<article>` | Independent content |
| `<aside>`   | Sidebar content     |
| `<footer>`  | Footer section      |

ğŸ“Œ Improves readability, SEO, and accessibility

